e atlas of Hinkle, etc., whose scale is\nshifted and depends on the wavelength. In the range from 450 to 650 nm, the\nscale shift of this atlas varies from -100 to -330 m/s, respectively, and it\nequals on average of -240 m/s. The resulting average star bisectors contain\ninformation about the fields of convective velocities and may be useful for\nhydrodynamic modeling of stellar atmospheres in order to study the\ncharacteristic features of surface convection.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 26 Dec 2020 18:12:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-31"}
